The paper deals with mechanism design in social choice protocols and multiagent systems, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT). The paper specifically focuses on weighted voting games, which are a type of coalitional game, and examines manipulations in these games, which is a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multiagent systems (cs.MA). The paper also provides algorithms and computational complexity analysis, which are topics that fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
